---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Me">
  <style lang="scss">
    body {
        background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #fff0f5, #ffffff);
    }

    .about-container {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        background: white;
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: 1rem;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
        pacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(20px);
        animation: fadeIn 0.6s ease-out 0.1s forwards;

        @keyframes fadeIn {
            to {
                opacity: 1;
                transform: none;
            }
      }


      @media (min-width: 768px) {
        flex-direction: row;
        align-items: flex-start;
      }

      img {
        width: 18rem;
        height: 18rem;
        border-radius: 50%;
        object-fit: cover;
      }

      .about-text {
        max-width: 600px;
      }

      $highlight-pinks: (
        #e91e63,
        #f06292,
        #ec407a,
        #f48fb1,
        #ff80ab,
        #ff4081
      );

      @for $i from 1 through length($highlight-pinks) {
        .about-text .hl-#{$i} {
          color: nth($highlight-pinks, $i);
          font-weight: bold;
        }
      }
    }
  </style>

  <h1 style="text-align: center;">About Me</h1>

  <div class="about-container">
    <img src="/maud.jpg" alt="Photo of Me" />

    <div class="about-text">
      <p>
        I’m a <span class="hl-1">full-stack software engineer</span> who thrives on turning real problems into <span class="hl-2">user-friendly solutions</span>. I’ve worked across the stack—from Java and Groovy backends to React and Electron frontends. I move quickly, learn fast, and adapt to the problem at hand.
      </p>

      <p>
        I’ve <span class="hl-3">led feature development</span>, <span class="hl-4">authored internal documentation</span>, and <span class="hl-5">kept teams motivated</span> while shipping clean systems.
      </p>

      <p>
        I currently work with <span class="hl-6">React, TypeScript, and PostgreSQL</span>, often in privacy-conscious or healthcare-adjacent projects. I care about clean interfaces, ethical tech, and reducing complexity.
      </p>

      <p>
        I value <span class="hl-1">honing the craft</span>—not just shipping what “works.” Code should be understandable, maintainable, and a little elegant under pressure.
      </p>

      <p>
        Outside of code, I paint surreal things, hike in the mountains, and occasionally commit culinary crimes. :)
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
